  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Predicate

    public class Type
extends TaxonomyPredicate
    The Type class represents data type/format that can be used by our tools. Type can be an actual data type or an abstraction class.
    Author:
    Vedran Kasalica

      • generateType

        public static Type generateType(java.lang.String typeName,
                                java.lang.String typeID,
                                java.lang.String rootType,
                                NodeType nodeType,
                                AllTypes allTypes,
                                Type superType)
        The class is used to check weather the type with typeID was already introduced earlier on in allTypes. In case it was, it returns the item, otherwise the new element is generated and returned.

        In case of generating a new Type, the object is added to the set of all the Types and added as a subType to the parent Type.
        Parameters:
        typeName - - Type name
        typeID - - Unique Type identifier
        rootType - - Determines whether the Type is a simple/leaf type
        nodeType - - NodeType object describing the type w.r.t. the Type Taxonomy.
        allTypes - - Set of all the types created
        superType - - The Parent (abstract) Type of the current Type
        Returns:
        The Type object.
